data.title: Brian McFadden: I’m happy to be flying without savings

data.text:
In 2004, Brian McFadden shocked legions of his predominantly young female fans by quitting Westlife when the Irish boy band were at the height of their fame.

Dublin-born McFadden, now 37, went on to forge a successful career as a solo artist, talent show judge and television presenter, and spent nearly a decade living in Australia.

He has had several high-profile relationships — with the likes of the former Atomic Kitten singer Kerry Katona, the Australian singer-songwriter Delta Goodrem and the model Vogue Williams — and has two teenage daughters: Molly, 16, and Lily-Sue, 14. He now lives in Rochdale with his partner Danielle Parkinson, a PE teacher.
